column9: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Unique Users)
column10: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Total Count)
column11: Lifetime: The number of unique people who engaged in certain ways with your Page post, for example by commenting on, liking, sharing, or clicking upon particular elements of the post. (Unique Users)
column12: Lifetime: The number of clicks anywhere in your post on News Feed from the user that matched the audience targeting on it. (Total Count)
column13: Lifetime: The number of impressions of your Page post to people who have liked your Page. (Total Count)
column14: Lifetime: The number of people who like your Page and who saw your Page post in an ad or sponsored story. (Unique Users)
column15: Lifetime: The number of people who have liked your Page and clicked anywhere in your posts. (Unique Users)

column3:
COMEDY IMPROV SHOW! Could we get a suggestion? 'BIOMEDICINE'! https://www.popup-lab.com

Once upon a time, a group of Improvisers asked themselves: 
Can science be fun… and scientists funny🤔? 

Find out the answer by watching our newest POP UP concept: science and improv 🧬. POP UP LAB is an innovative show where improvisers and scientists take the audience on a hilarious—and completely improvised—journey of discovery through scientific breakthroughs with the aim to discredit pseudo-science and manufactured controversies. 💻
Improv is a form of theatre made up on the spot. It’s interactive, effervescent...and fun! And POP UP LAB argues the need for a ‘natural’ embedding of science in society in an informal and relaxed format through improvisation: a bridge from the academic "ivory tower" to the wider public.
